edu.uidaho.junicon.runtime.junicon.iterators

Interface IIconUndo<T>


  • public interface IIconUndo<T>
    Save and restore the environment for an undoable action. An iterator will undo the action and fail if it is resumed, i.e., if next() occurs and it is non-empty with count > 0.

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Default Methods
